    <briefdescription>
<para>Simple class for passing around pairs of small integers. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Use this for integer dimensions and points with limited range such as image sizes and pixel coordinates where a pair of floating point numbers is inefficient and illogical (i.e. the data is inherently integer).</para>
<para>For example in IntPair&lt;uint16_t&gt; one of these can be passed in a single 32 bit integer register on common architectures.</para>
<para>@SINCE_2_1.45 <parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>tIntType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The signed/unsigned integer type for get/set access. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>tUintType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The unsigned integer type that will be stored. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>tDataType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The 2-tuple stored integer type. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
